      "rationale": "Mesh convergence study performed across three refinement levels (coarse: ~85k elements, medium: ~210k elements, fine: ~520k elements). Richardson extrapolation applied to stiffness and yield force QoIs. Grid convergence index (GCI) < 1.5% for all QoIs at the medium mesh, which was adopted for production runs. Required level 3 reflects that contact mechanics at the screw-rod interface are sensitive to mesh density. Acceptance criterion: GCI < 2% for all primary QoIs at production mesh density."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
