      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/ac/model-form-level3-pedicle-fea",
      "rationale": "Nonlinear elastic-plastic material model (bilinear isotropic hardening) applied to titanium alloy components. Contact interactions modeled with penalty-based frictional contact (μ=0.3) at all screw-rod and rod-block interfaces. Model form selection justified by literature review of validated pedicle screw FEA models. Required level 3 reflects the complexity of multi-body contact and nonlinear material behavior. Acceptance criterion: material model parameters validated against coupon-level tensile test data; contact formulation validated against independent analytical estimate of construct stiffness."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/ac/model-inputs-level3-pedicle-fea",
      "rationale": "Material properties (E=114 GPa, σy=880 MPa, tangent modulus=1.1 GPa for Ti-6Al-4V) sourced from ASTM F136 lot-specific certification data for the tested specimens. Geometric dimensions taken from CMM measurements of each test specimen (±0.01 mm). Boundary conditions replicate ASTM F1717 fixture geometry as measured. Input uncertainty quantified via Monte Carlo propagation over material property distributions. Required level 3 is consistent with medium model risk and the need to bound input uncertainty contributions to total model error. Acceptance criterion: input uncertainty contribution to total QoI uncertainty < 30% as assessed by variance-based sensitivity analysis."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/ac/test-samples-level3-pedicle-fea",
      "rationale": "N=11 non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw constructs tested across two independent laboratories. Specimens drawn from production lots; dimensional and material certification records available. Sample size sufficient to characterize inter-specimen variability (CV < 5% for stiffness). Required level 3 reflects the need for statistically meaningful comparison across two laboratories. Acceptance criterion: N ≥ 10 specimens with full dimensional and material traceability; inter-laboratory reproducibility assessed via ANOVA (p > 0.05 for lab effect on primary QoIs)."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "rationale": "Testing performed under a single load configuration (compression-bending per ASTM F1717). Only one test condition evaluated; torsion and fatigue conditions not included in this validation activity. Achieved level 2 because the validation covers a single standardized test condition without variation in load angle or rate."
    },
    {
