      "rationale": "Model inputs mapped directly to measured specimen properties. Good equivalency established."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/ac/output-comparison-level3-pedicle-fea",
      "rationale": "Quantitative comparison performed for three primary QoIs (construct stiffness, yield force, force at 40 mm displacement) using the validation metric E/uval per ASME V&V 40 Section 9. All E/uval values < 1.96 (95% confidence bound). Percent differences: stiffness 4.2%, yield force 8.3%, F40mm 6.7%. Required level 3 reflects that a quantitative, uncertainty-normalized metric is needed for a medium model risk COU. Acceptance criterion: E/uval < 1.96 and percent difference < 10% for all three primary QoIs across all 11 specimens."
    },
